{
  "texts": [
    "Our Appendix 3.2 provides further details on the coding methodology and development process for the taxonomy structure categorized into legal, technical, psychological, behavioral and ethical critiques.",
    "As a clarification, recitals shall serve to elaborate Article objectives without constituting obligations.",
    "Thereby their role is unambiguously scoped for reader understanding.",
    "Within this perspective, Recital 56 reproves particulary useful while discussing monitoring barriers on platform that could \"set the rules of the game, without effectively identifying and mitigating the risks and the societal and economic harm they can cause\".",
    "Hereby, research audit studies as used here refer to independent experiments by researchers, distinct from mandated DSA compliance audits in Article 37 and the Delegated Act[50]."
  ]
}